glad — vendored OpenGL function loader (generated, committed)
=============================================================

This is a *generated* GL loader, vendored per CLAUDE.md's dependency policy: GLFW is the
only runtime dependency; glad is build-time only and ships nothing extra into the binary.
The generated sources are committed (not fetched) so builds are reproducible without a
network round-trip or a Python toolchain.

Generation parameters
----------------------
  Generator : glad 1.x  (the "glad1" / classic generator, NOT glad2)
  API       : gl = 3.3
  Profile   : core
  Language  : c
  Spec      : Khronos OpenGL-Registry gl.xml
  Extensions: none

Command (reproduce from a clean checkout)
-----------------------------------------
  pip install "glad<2"
  python -m glad --profile core --api gl=3.3 --generator c --reproducible \
      --out-path third_party/glad

Files
-----
  include/glad/glad.h      core GL 3.3 declarations + loader prototypes
  include/KHR/khrplatform.h
  src/glad.c               the loader implementation

Usage
-----
  glad1 exposes a self-contained loader, gladLoadGL(), that resolves GL entry points via
  the platform GL library (opengl32.dll on Windows, libGL on Linux). CodePhys calls it
  after the GLFW context is made current (see platform/src/window.cpp). Using gladLoadGL()
  rather than gladLoadGLLoader((GLADloadproc)glfwGetProcAddress) keeps our first-party
  code free of the function-pointer <-> object-pointer cast that -Wpedantic -Werror would
  reject; glad.c itself is compiled without our strict warnings.

Do not edit the generated files by hand. To change the GL version/profile, re-run the
command above and update this README.
